[[File:Moroccan preserved dried meat-Khli-01.jpg|thumb|Moroccan preserved dried meat-Khli-01]] '''Khlea''' or '''khlii''' is a preserved meat, usually made with beef or lamb, originating from [[Morocco]].<ref name="Pintsize">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pintsizegourmets.com/khlea-moroccos-preserved-meat/|title=All About Khlea: Morocco’s Preserved Meat|date=2016-06-17|work=Pint Size Gourmets|access-date=2018-03-31|language=en-US}}</ref> Khlea is made by cutting meat into strips and letting it dry in the sun after marinating it in [[garlic]], [[coriander]] and [[cumin]].<ref name="Dried Meat">{{Cite web|url=https://dafina.net/viandesechee_en.htm|title=Dried meat : Khlii|website=dafina.net|access-date=2018-03-31}}</ref> The meat is cooked in a mixture of water, oil and animal fat.<ref name="Spruce">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thespruce.com/khlea-khlii-preserved-meat-2394626|title=How Preserved Meat Is Used on Moroccan Food|work=The Spruce|access-date=2018-03-31}}</ref> Upon cooling, the meat is submerged in more animal fat and left to dry. Khlea can be preserved for up to two years at [[room temperature]].<ref name="Taste">{{Cite news|url=https://tasteofmaroc.com/moroccan-preserved-meat-khlii-khlea/|title=Moroccan Preserved Meat - Khlii or Khlea|date=2017-09-08|work=Taste of Maroc|access-date=2018-03-31|language=en-US}}</ref>
